HEADER STRUCTURE (From Image 1):
Row 1: County Name | EZ Accounting Count | Inventory Count | Count
       ^Column A   | ^Column B           | ^Column C       | ^Column D
                   | (has other words)   | (has other words)| (EXACTLY "Count")

LOGIC:
1. Loop through columns B to last column
2. Check each header
3. Find the one that is EXACTLY "Count" (no other text)
4. Mark that column as the Total column
5. Sum all columns BEFORE it
6. Exclude the "Count" column from sum

